<TITLE> JMB chief's wife, in-law arrested </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 1 (bdnews24.com)--The RAB on Sunday detained the wife and sister-in-law of Jama'atul Mujahideen Bangladesh's linchpin who narrowly evaded arrest at East Goran in the capital. RAB-3's operation officer Captain Taifur Rahman told bdnews24.com that they arrested Maulana Saidur Rahman's second wife Himu, 25 and his brother in law's wife Mimi,18, in a raid on a rented house at East Goran under Sabujbagh Police Station at around 6pm. He said Saidur had left the house only 20 minutes before the drive. Twenty five SIMs, Jihadi literatur, and books on bomb-making, CDs and papers on the funds of the banned Islamist outfit were also recovered from them, he further said. Saidur has been spearheading the militants since the execution of JMB founder Shaokh Abdur Rahman with five others in 2007. b
